        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 4:38AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 437 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hearne, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
College Station, Bryan, Kurten, Wixon Valley, Kyle Field, Bryan
Utilities Lake, and Wellborn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
